cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation and feature extraction. It may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it involves the classification of objects in images. The use of machine learning techniques for feature extraction and classification suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of color and texture features suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a majority voting strategy for segmentation suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
